article.headline: Coppin St. 63, Howard 56
article.story: WASHINGTON -- Patrick Cole scored eight of his 14 points in the final 3:07 as Coppin State defeated Howard 63-56 Saturday to end a seven-game losing streak. Michael Murray, who scored 16 points for the Eagles (6-22, 3-10 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference), got nine during a 17-6 run to start the second half that gave Coppin State a 48-33 lead. Taariq Cephas, who finished with 14 points for Coppin State, along with Andre Armstrong, had seven points during the run. The Bison (6-22, 3-11) cut Coppin State's lead to 56-53 with 2:55 left but got no closer as they lost their fourth straight. Two consecutive jumpers by Cole made it 60-53 at the 1:05 mark. Mike Phillips had 12 points and 11 rebounds for Howard, and Tre Lee and Anton Dickerson scored 11 each. The Bison had a 49-38 rebounding advantage but were hurt by 10 second-half turnovers.
